### Notes

*   Data for Afghanistan, Lebanon, Palestine, and Sri Lanka are from 2024.
*   The [European Union](/Economy_of_the_European_Union) is included due to its unique status as more than a simple trade bloc. It possesses attributes of a state, including its own [flag](/Flag_of_Europe), [anthem](/Anthem_of_Europe), [currency](/Euro) (for [some members](/Eurozone)), [parliament](/European_Parliament), [law-making abilities](/Institutions_of_the_European_Union), and [diplomatic representation](/Diplomatic_missions_of_the_European_Union). However, as an [organization](/Organization) rather than a [sovereign state](/Sovereign_state), it is not ranked.
*   Data for [Cyprus](/Economy_of_Cyprus) represent the area controlled by the Government of the [Republic of Cyprus](/Cyprus).
*   The [IMF](/International_Monetary_Fund) refers to Taiwan as the "Taiwan Province of China."
*   Figures for [China](/Economy_of_China) exclude [Taiwan](/Taiwan), [Hong Kong](/Hong_Kong), and [Macau](/Macau).
*   Excludes [Abkhazia](/Abkhazia) and [South Ossetia](/South_Ossetia).
*   Excludes data for [Transnistria](/Transnistria).
*   Figures exclude the [Autonomous Republic of Crimea](/Autonomous_Republic_of_Crimea) and [Sevastopol](/Sevastopol).
*   The [IMF](/International_Monetary_Fund) and [World Bank](/World_Bank) use the designation "West Bank and Gaza."
*   The [United Nations](/United_Nations) refers to the area as the "State of Palestine."
*   The [UN](/United_Nations) figure excludes the autonomous region of [Zanzibar](/Zanzibar).

